<plot>This is a musical biography of band-vocalist 'Patty Clayton' (qv), nee Patti Clayton, told by band-leader 'Paul Whiteman (I)' (qv). It traces her singing career from her girlhood to her present position among the nation's top female singers. When she gets an opportunity to sing, and be heard nationwide, over the CBS radio-network in New York City, she develops a serious illness. But she recovers and returns to New York and takes her place among the best.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?382484</url></doc>
